<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="rosetta">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-groups" />
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-stats" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-preflangs" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <h1>Welcome to Rosetta!</h1>

    <p>
      Rosetta is a Web-based system for translating open source software into
      any language. You can read more <a href="+about" title="About Rosetta">
      about Rosetta</a> or follow the links below to start translating.
    </p>

    <h2>Translations in Ubuntu</h2>

    <p>Rosetta is the primary translation system for the Ubuntu Project. You
    can help to translate any application in Ubuntu, or any of the Ubuntu
    derivative distributions, using this web interface. Select a release
    from the list below:</p>
    
    <div style="margin-left: 50px;">

      <p tal:repeat="distrorelease context/translatable_distroreleases">
        <img src="/++resource++product_icon.gif">
        <b><span tal:replace="distrorelease/version" />: "<span
        tal:replace="distrorelease/title">distrorelease
        title</span>"</b>&nbsp;[&nbsp;<a tal:attributes="href
        string:/distros/${distrorelease/distribution/name}/${distrorelease/name}/+translations">Translate</a>&nbsp;]
        <br />
        <span tal:replace="distrorelease/summary">product
        summary</span>
      </p>

    </div> <!-- indent -->

    <h2>Translatable Applications</h2>

    <p>Rosetta is being used to translate the following open source
    applications. Select an application to translate it into your
    own language, using only your web browser. If your favourite open
    source application is not listed here, you can see
    if it is <a href="/products/">registered with the Launchpad</a> and then
    ask the Rosetta Admins on <a
    href="mailto:rosetta-users@lists.ubuntu.com">Rosetta's mailing list</a>
    to import its translation templates so you can begin to translate
    immediately!</p>

    <table class="listing">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Application</th>
          <th>Title</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr tal:repeat="product context/translatable_products">
          <td><img src="/++resource++product_icon.gif"> <span tal:replace="product/name">product</span></td>
          
          <td><a href="." tal:content="product/title"
                 tal:attributes="href
                     string:/products/${product/name}/+translations">
                     Product Title here</a></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Find or register <a href="/products/">any other open source
    application</a> for translation.</p>

</div>

</body>
</html>
